---
export const updateMeta = {
  date: '2026-05-29',
  title: "New Let's Connect page with interest routing and thoughtful auto-reply",
  tags: ['lead-capture', 'forms', 'auto-reply', 'expo'],
};
---
<article class="border-l-4 border-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] pl-6">
  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-1">May 29, 2026</h2>
  <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-4">Launched a permanent <a href="/lets-connect" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/lets-connect</a> page so anyone (visitors at expos, casual website traffic, breeders, providers, breed clubs, future buyers) can drop their info and get a thoughtful, tailored response. Designed to be tablet-friendly for in-person events and equally at home as an always-on site link.</p>

  <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">New page</h3>
  <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 list-disc pl-6 mb-4 space-y-1">
    <li><a href="/lets-connect" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/lets-connect</a>: short form (Name, Email, Phone/WhatsApp, an "I'm interested in..." single-select, optional message) with a "What happens next" section setting expectations around the personal follow-up.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">"I'm interested in..." options</h3>
  <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 list-disc pl-6 mb-4 space-y-1">
    <li>Managing my breeding operation</li>
    <li>Offering my services to breeders</li>
    <li>Helping my organization or club manage membership &amp; records</li>
    <li>Finding a breeder or available animal</li>
    <li>Listing animals for sale</li>
    <li>Genetic testing &amp; health records</li>
    <li>Just browsing / tell me more</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Auto-reply</h3>
  <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-4">Submitters get an immediate styled email from <code>hello@mail.breederhq.com</code> (reply-to <code>info@breederhq.com</code>) with copy tailored to whichever interest they selected. Different next-step links surface for breeders vs. providers vs. organizations vs. buyers vs. browsers. The auto-reply opts in by source value (<code>lets_connect</code>) so the existing <a href="/contact" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/contact</a> form behavior is unchanged.</p>

  <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Internal notifications</h3>
  <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-4">The existing lead pipeline (Slack, Resend notification to info@breederhq.com, HubSpot, Zapier, Clearbit enrichment) carries the new <code>interest</code> field through unchanged paths. Every channel now shows the selected interest alongside name, email, phone, and message.</p>

  <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Navigation</h3>
  <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 list-disc pl-6 mb-4 space-y-1">
    <li>Footer Resources column now links to <a href="/lets-connect" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">Let's Connect</a> directly under <a href="/contact" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">Contact Us</a>, giving the page a permanent home on every page of the site.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Why this exists</h3>
  <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">The Contact Us form is generic. Let's Connect is conversational, designed for the moment someone hands a tablet to a booth visitor or a curious site visitor clicks through from a CTA. Capturing intent up front (single radio choice) lets the auto-reply and the personal follow-up actually be helpful instead of generic. No CRM or database changes were needed; leads flow through the existing distribution pipeline.</p>
</article>
